**Debug The given Code**

**Objective:**
Fix scope-related issues in a piece of broken code.
Scenario:
The following code is throwing errors. Fix the code using proper scoping rules and best practices.
**Code:**
```js
function testScope() {
  if (true) {
    var name = "Alice";
    let age = 25;
    const city = "New York";
  }
  console.log(name); // Works
  console.log(age); // Error: ReferenceError
  console.log(city); // Error: ReferenceError
}
testScope();
```

**Instructions:**
1. Submit the code first and see the error
2. Comment out or remove the if condition so that the code starts to work.

